Introduction¶

TMDb movie data: I've selected the TMDb movie dataset for analysis. This data set contains information about 10,000 movies collected from The Movie Database (TMDb), including user ratings and revenue.

  • The processes will include the following:
    1. Import data and try to find all details by looking into data set
    2. Wrangling : clean, renaming, datatypes converting and outliers removing for Dataset.
    3. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA): after preparing dataset for exploring, I will try to anwser question to identify coreelations between different features of dataset. the finding will be around the analysis of at least one dependent variable and three independent variables.

Data Cleaning¶

Finiding in Cleaning Data Process:¶

  1. Most columns names were already renamed, they didn't have no spaces and all lowercase in names
  2. Datatypes didn't need much converting or more processing.
  3. There are some fields that didn't have proper values such as earning. this fields as value with negative values.
  4. There are some fields removed that didn't add much difference such as:
    • imdb_id
    • homepage
    • tagline
    • keywords
    • overview
    • production_companies
  5. There are a spereation in datasets. The new dataset df_genres contains a new field genres_seperate for all genres found in one row. This new field will allow proper view of data.
  6. As per upper guidlines, I added all commands in aggregated rows.

""" 
deal with genres field to get the most benefit out from data frame
    1. Copy Data Frame
    2. Split the genres & assign to the new variabel
    3. rename the the header
    4. delete the old column
"""
df_genres = df.copy()
df_genres_f = df_genres['genres'].str.split('|').apply(pd.Series, 1).stack().reset_index(level=1, drop=True)
df_genres_f.name = 'genre_seperate'
df_genres = df_genres.drop(['genres'], axis=1).join(df_genres_f)
In [14]:
"""
Create a grouping for every 10 years in the whole period

"""
Create an earning column which will be as follow:
    1- earning = revenu - budjet
    2. replace earning < 0 with value = 0
    3. calculate earning percetage
    4. solve the issue of revenue = 0

"""
df['earning']=df['revenue'] - df['budget']
df['earning'].isnull().sum()
df[df['earning']<0]
df.loc[df['earning']<0,'earning']=0
#as there is a revenu with 0 values, it's impossible to caluculate % of earning
df[df['revenue']==0]
#add a small value to the base to allow division
df['earn_percentage'] = round((df['earning']/(df['revenue']+.001))*100,2)
df['earn_percentage'].unique()

array([90.09, 60.36, 62.74, ..., 76.92, 22.45, 57.37])

Conclusions¶

  1. Genres like Drama, Comedy, Thriller, and Action are about 50% of all movies made over years.
  2. Action was the most poular movie.
  3. List of 20 top earning movies
  4. Runtime decreased over years from 115 to 97 on average.
  5. top 20 of popular movies
  6. The average Earnings % over years
  7. List of directors who can gain more earning
  8. List of top revenue movies over years in revenue

Limitations¶

  1. As the data for old movies is not fully provided for budjet and revenue features. This will affact on the accuracy of the results.
  2. I have added some values to solve the issue of revenue = 0. This will facilitate the calculation of earning feature
  3. There is no much information about technology, it's was just a site added to the fields
  4. The file that is used already has the solution for most of issues related to:
    • lower case / no spaces fields names
    • release year already extracted from release date
    • most of values in a well format, with proper type
